definitions.definition: A statement expressing opposition , or a reason or cause for expressing opposition (generally followed by the adposition to ).
examples: I have no objection to any person's religion.

definitions.definition: An official protest raised in a court of law during a legal trial over a violation of the rules of the court by the opposing party.
